lead_paragraph: Asian shares and commodity currencies dropped on Thursday as investor concerns about a slowing Chinese economy eclipsed optimism over the U.S. outlook, while Tokyo stocks stepped back after posting large gains in a Bank of Japan-inspired rally.

headline.main: Asian Shares Slip as China Concerns Trump U.S. Optimism
